The ANC in Parliament has confirmed the resignation of former minister of tourism Derek Hanekom as a member of Parliament. He becomes the latest former minister to resign as a legislator in the National Assembly. Hanekom failed to make the cut when President Cyril Ramaphosa announced his Cabinet two weeks ago. Earlier on Tuesday,  former Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini also stepped down as an MP in an eight-page resignation letter. So far, 15 former ministers have decided not to take up their seats.
